# plinking_duck roadmap

Sequenced plan for the next few releases. Shipped features are in the git history
and `PLAN-INDEX`; this file is the forward view. Ordering is a recommendation —
the writer-vs-ergonomics timing (v0.9 ↔ v0.10) is the main open call.

## Shipped

- **v0.7.x** — multi-file/sharded reads, `combine_samples`, shared `psam`;
  `file_search_path`/glob/`pathmacro:` resolution; region-zero-match crash fix;
  streaming per-sample counts/stats + optional sparse (difflist) carrier path;
  plink2-wrapping audit (chrX HWE fix, vendored-extract pinning + drift canary).
- **v0.8.0** — **remote / VFS `.pgen` reads** (s3://, http, pathmacro:,
  file_search_path) across every reader + analysis function, via a `fopencookie`
  shim on pgenlib + a read-ahead block cache; `plinking_pgen_io` policy. Ahead of
  the plink2 CLI (local-only). Design: `P12-001-*`.

## v0.8.1 — complete the remote story (patch)

Small, no-fork follow-ups that round out P12. Good first release after v0.8.0.

- **macOS CI** — ✅ **DONE.** Both macOS arches (`osx_amd64`, `osx_arm64`) built
  green on the community-CI job for #2298 — the `funopen` branch's first real
  compile passed, no fix needed.
- **`localize` (opt-in, configurable)** — ✅ **DONE** (branch
  `feature/v0.8.1-localize`). `plinking_pgen_io := 'localize'` materializes a local
  temp copy of the `.pgen` at bind (via the context FS → httpfs secrets apply),
  rewrites the path, reads natively — the good answer for remote *full scans*.
  Explicit opt-in: `auto` never localizes. Configurable temp dir
  (`plinking_localize_dir`, defaults to DuckDB's `temporary_directory`, created if
  missing); per-query temp lifecycle via a move-only `PgenLocalizeGuard` in each
  reader's bind data (unlinked when the query ends). Design decision: `localize`
  **always copies, even a local source** — so the chunked-copy path is testable
  without a network (`test/sql/read_pfile_localize.test`, localize==native across
  the reader/analysis surface, incl. a no-op guard: an uncreatable temp dir MUST
  error, proving the copy actually runs). **Remote path validated end-to-end**: a
  local Range-capable HTTP server + the bundled httpfs → `localize` over
  `http://…/wes_chr10.pgen` (10.5 MB, 3 copy chunks) is byte-identical to native,
  temp unlinked after the query. **Deferred (known cuts):** no size/threshold guard
  (downloads an arbitrarily large remote `.pgen` in full — reach for it
  deliberately); no persistent URL→temp cache (per-query only; `cache_httpfs`
  covers repeat-query at the block layer). Design notes:
  `P12-001-implementation-notes`.
- **`.pgi` split-index** — companion-discover a `.pgi` and thread `pgi_fname`
  (currently always `nullptr` = embedded-index only). Non-fork compat fix; the
  `.pgi` rides the existing VFS shim. See `P12-001-remote-vfs-pgen-reads` §0a.
- *(stretch)* shared cross-reader block cache — only if a real multi-thread
  remote-scan workload shows the per-thread index re-read hurting (localize +
  `cache_httpfs` cover most of it first).

## v0.9.0 — query ergonomics + GWAS convenience (feature)

Cohesive "nicer queries, easier GWAS" release. Moderate effort, no vendored fork.

- **P10 filter pushdown** — a `WHERE` clause drives the reader's existing
  region/af/ac/sample/genotype filters (`WHERE CHROM='17' AND POS BETWEEN …` runs
  the region pushdown). Idiomatic SQL, and the enabler for efficient ATTACH views.
  Design: `P10-001-filter-pushdown`. Risk: consumed-vs-residual filter reporting.
  Gated by a new **`plinking_pushdown_mode`** setting:
  - `'none'` — no pushdown (post-scan filtering only; the pre-P10 behavior).
  - `'standard'` *(default, v0.9.0)* — `WHERE` → region/af/ac/sample/genotype filters.
  - `'smart'` — *(v0.11.0+)* also **infer read config from column references**: a
    query touching `variants.<ID>` / `samples.<IID>` / `genotype.<field>` auto-
    configures the corresponding `variants :=` / `samples :=` / genotype selection
    on `read_pfile`, so column access drives what's read. More speculative
    (projection→config inference); deferred past `'standard'`.
- **P2-007 `plink_phenotype` + GLM psam column refs** — `plink_glm(…, phenotype :=
  'height')` reads the phenotype/covariates from a `.psam` column instead of a
  separate join. Removes the most common GWAS friction. Design: `P2-007-*`.

## v0.10.0 — the pfile WRITER (headline feature)

The biggest earmarked capability: make plinking_duck **read *and* write**.
`COPY (SELECT … ORDER BY chrom,pos) TO 'prefix' (FORMAT pfile, variant_fields:={…},
sample_fields:={…}, genotype_fields:=…)`. Design + both feasibility spikes are
**green** (`P9-001-writers-design` + `P9-002-writers-implementation-plan`, on the
archived `feature/reader-completion` branch); build not started. Brings in
pgenlib's write path (currently excluded), same `FILE*`-local-only constraint as
the reader (so a remote writer waits, like `localize`).

**Modular — write any subset, not just the bundle:**
- Individual `.pvar` / `.psam` / `.pgen` writers (e.g. `FORMAT pvar`/`psam`/`pgen`,
  or `write_pvar`/`write_psam`/`write_pgen`) AND the bundled `FORMAT pfile`.
- Options to **also emit companions**: `.pgi` (split index) and/or
  `.pvar.parquet` / `.psam.parquet` (parquet companions), so the output is
  round-trippable by the reader's fast paths.

Build order A→E: CopyFunction scaffold + text `.pvar`/`.psam` writers → `.pgen`
(+ optional `.pgi`) → pfile bundle (+ optional parquet companions) → shard wrapper
→ plink-VCF. Only a **plink-flavored** text VCF (biallelic, GT-only, zero-dep) is
in scope here; **spec-grade VCF/BCF is delegated to duckhts** (below). Its own
release given the size. *(Could move to v0.9.0 if the writer is the priority over
ergonomics — the main open sequencing call.)*

## Deferred — VCF/BCF export via duckhts (BLOCKED on their write path)

**Not a plinking_duck writer.** Real (multiallelic, INFO, bgzf, csi/tbi-indexed)
VCF/BCF is delegated to **duckhts** (htslib-backed; *not* our repo — friendly
maintainer). duckhts is **read-only today** (all `read_*`); this item is **blocked
until duckhts adds a `COPY … TO (FORMAT vcf/bcf)` write path**. Revisit then.

Interop, when unblocked (SQL-level only — two extensions can't link each other's
C++; they compose through SQL, both must be `LOAD`ed):
- duckhts's `tidy_format := true` schema (`CHROM,POS,ID,REF,ALT,QUAL,FILTER,INFO_*,
  SAMPLE_ID,FORMAT_GT,…`) == our `orient := 'genotype'` grain. Bridge is
  column-rename + one transform.
- **Our side (cheap, could ship independently as a helper even now):**
  - `plink_gt(genotype)` — vectorized scalar: unphased `0/1/2/-9→'0/0'/'0/1'/'1/1'/'./.'`,
    phased `[a,b]→'a|b'`. The only real logic; runs per genotype cell → C++ scalar,
    not a SQL CASE macro.
  - `read_pfile_vcf(prefix,…)` / `to_vcf_rows` table macro — wraps `read_pfile(…,
    orient:='genotype')`, projects to duckhts's tidy schema (`IID→SAMPLE_ID`,
    `plink_gt(genotype)→FORMAT_GT`). Then `COPY (SELECT * FROM read_pfile_vcf(…))
    TO 'out.vcf.gz' (FORMAT vcf)`.
- **Coordinate before building:** confirm duckhts's write contract — does it consume
  `FORMAT_GT` as the same **string** form (vs. ints / wide layout)? And **header
  construction** (`##contig`/INFO/FORMAT defs) lives on *their* side (htslib
  `bcf_hdr_*`, inferred or templated) — our helpers only shape the tidy body.
- Draft a write-path-contract note to the maintainer once we pick this back up.

## v0.11.0+ — catalog + population genetics (later)

- **P11 ATTACH pfile catalog** — `ATTACH 'cohort' AS c (TYPE plink)` exposing
  `c.variants` / `c.samples` / `c.genotypes` / `c.freq` / … as a schema of views.
  Spike-gated; **depends on P10** (views need WHERE-pushdown to be flexible) and
  reads best **after the writer** (so it can unify read + write of a fileset as one
  attachable database). Cheap interim: a `plink_attach()` view/macro helper to
  validate demand first. Design: `P11-001-attach-pfile-catalog`.
- **Deferred analysis functions** (demand-driven): `plink_king_table` (kinship,
  O(N²)), `plink_het`, `plink_fst`. See PLAN-INDEX "Deferred Candidates".

